# Security Guidelines

> This rule was auto-generated by Claude harness.
> Purpose: Detect changes that require security attention and present a checklist.

## Patterns Requiring Security Attention

### File Path Detection

| Path Pattern | Attention Level | Reason |
|-------------|----------------|--------|
| `src/auth/`, `auth/` | High | Authentication logic |
| `src/api/`, `api/`, `routes/` | Medium | API endpoints |
| `middleware/` | Medium | Request handling |
| `src/payment/`, `billing/` | High | Payment processing |
| `config/`, `.env*` | Medium | Sensitive configuration |

### Code Change Patterns

| Pattern | Attention Level | Reason |
|---------|----------------|--------|
| `password`, `secret`, `token` | High | Credentials |
| Dynamic code evaluation functions | High | Arbitrary code execution risk |
| SQL query string concatenation | High | SQL injection |
| React raw HTML insertion | Medium | XSS risk |
| `cors()` configuration changes | Medium | Cross-origin |

## OWASP Top 10 Checklist

### When Changing Authentication/Authorization

- [ ] **A01: Broken Access Control**
  - Authorization checks present on all endpoints
  - Role-based access control is correct

- [ ] **A02: Cryptographic Failures**
  - Passwords are hashed (bcrypt, argon2)
  - Sensitive data is encrypted
  - HTTPS is enforced

- [ ] **A07: Identification and Authentication Failures**
  - Brute force protection (rate limiting)
  - Session management is appropriate
  - MFA support considered

### When Changing APIs

- [ ] **A03: Injection**
  - Input values are sanitized
  - Parameterized queries are used
  - Command injection prevention

- [ ] **A04: Insecure Design**
  - Principle of least privilege
  - Input validation at the business logic level

- [ ] **A05: Security Misconfiguration**
  - No unnecessary endpoints exposed
  - Error messages not overly detailed
  - Default credentials have been changed

### When Changing Dependencies

- [ ] **A06: Vulnerable and Outdated Components**
  - No known vulnerabilities in added packages (`npm audit`)
  - Versions are up to date
  - Package is actively maintained

## Decision Logic for Skills

```
File change detected
    |
Path pattern match
    |
    |-- auth/, api/, payment/ -> Show security checklist
    |-- middleware/ -> CORS, authorization check
    |-- .env*, config/ -> Sensitive information exposure check
    |-- Other -> Normal processing
```

## Suggestion Templates

**When authentication-related changes are detected**:
> Security: Authentication-related code changes detected.
> Please review the security checklist:
> - [ ] Password hashing
> - [ ] Session management
> - [ ] Rate limiting

**When API changes are detected**:
> Security: API endpoint changes detected.
> - [ ] Input validation
> - [ ] Authorization check
> - [ ] Error handling

